data.title: Marcus Rose
data.text:
Great Britain

Rugby

B: January 12, 1957

Member of the English National Team

Rose was a full back who played most of his career with Cambridge University. Rose made ten appearances for the English national team between 1981 and 1987, including the opening round match of the inaugural World Cup in 1987. However, Rose suffered a concussion in the first match, which would prove to be his last for the national team.
